frontend/Outdated/Advanced/Slides/intro.description: You can use pure Markdown, HTML, CSS or WLX languages while making slides

frontend/Outdated/Advanced/Slides/tables.description: One can utilize component InputTable, that originally stands for editing table, but can be used just to view them as well. frontend/Outdated/Cell types/Chatbook.title: Chatbook

To do this, you can simply enter .llm on the first line, and on the next line, any text

frontend/Outdated/Cell types/Many more...title: Many more...
frontend/Outdated/Cell types/Many more...description: You can extend output cell types via a few lines of code and you favorite framework / package

frontend/Outdated/Cell types/WLX.title: WLX

frontend/Outdated/Development/Decoration.title: Decorations
frontend/Outdated/Development/Decoration.description: You can think about it as a visual syntax sugar, which is similar to what one can see in VSCode, when one edits a CSS colors, the corresponding color picker popups allowing user to deal with color wheel instead of HEX color code.

frontend/Outdated/Development/Plugins/Kn.title: Known packages
frontend/Outdated/Development/Plugins/Kn.description: Here the symbol 🔶 means, that the package is shipped together with a basic WLJS Frontend distribution. Anything else can be installed separately from the Settings menu

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: Column
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: shows the list of any Wolfram Expressions in a single column acting as a decoration

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: Acts like a Style box, but wrapped into a frame

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: Grid
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: Spawns a grid of WL editors with an arbitrary objects inside

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: HTMLForm
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: renders HTML tags to the output cell

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: Interpretation
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: allows to alter the displayed expression

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: InterpretationBox
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: Make a formatting structure whose interpretation is not based on its appearance

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: BoxBox
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: Used to decorate Wolfram Expression with custom HTML elements

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: ViewBox
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: Used to replace wrapped Wolfram Expression with custom HTML elements

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: MakeBoxes
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: is a general expression used in UpValues of other expressions to change the visual representation (see Decorations) in the notebook.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: MatrixForm
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: shows the given matrix (list of lists) in a traditional form using Grid decoration

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: Row
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: shows the list of any Wolfram Expressions in a row acting as a decoration

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: Style
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: Styling box used as a decoration for an arbitrary Wolfram Expressions

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: SVGForm
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: exports as SVG any Wolfram Expressions and plots it inside a cell.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.title: TableForm
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Decorations/.description: shows the given table (list) in a traditional form using Grid decoration

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Cre.title: CreateFrontEndObject
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Cre.description: Creates a container for the inner expression and stores it into frontend objects storage shared with Kernel and Notebook

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Dyn.title: Dynamic
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Dyn.description: This concept is different from Mathematica. Please, use event-based approach instead - Dynamics

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Dyn.title: DynamicModule
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Dyn.description: This concept is different from Mathematica. Please, use event-based approach instead - Dynamics

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Fro.title: FrontEndVirtual
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Fro.description: It is a virtual container wrapper for any expressions evaluated on WLJS

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Fro.title: FrontSubmit
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Fro.description: Allows to execute any arbitrary WL code on frontend's (browser / client), where the notebook interface is displayed

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Int.title: FrontEndExecutable
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Int.description: An replacement decoration and a reference to the frontend object aka  container in the shared objects storage with a corresponding id

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Int.title: FrontEndExecutableInline
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Int.description: The same as FrontEndExecutable, but does not require a dedicated storage, the data is stored as a compressed string

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Int.title: FrontEndRef
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Int.description: An invisible replacement for FrontEndExecutable, which is not replaced by a widget in the editor and Wolfram Kernel.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Man.title: Manipulate
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Man.description: This is not supported. Please, use Dynamics instead

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Met.title: MetaMarker
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Met.description: A unique identifier or a reference of/to the container

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Off.title: Offload
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Dynamics/Off.description: Holds (or offloads) an expression to be evaluated on frontend (WLJS)

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Assig.title: Assign
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Assig.description: This is an experimental function. It might be changed or removed in the next updates

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Event.title: EventClone
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Event.description: clones an instance of ev event object passed as EventObject or a string with no interfering an original event handler function assigned to ev.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Event.title: EventFire
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Event.description: manually fires an event provided as EventObject or a string.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Event.title: EventHandler
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Event.description: assigns an handler function to an event object provided as a string or EventObject. The secondary functionality is

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Event.title: EventJoin
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Event.description: joins two or more events passed as EventObjects or strings into a new joined event object. For EventObjects a standard Wolfram Language expression Join works as well

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Event.title: EventObject
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Event.description: a local representation of event entity used in Dynamics,  Input elements and event-generators. It does provide extra feature to an event system such as listed below

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Event.title: EventRemove
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Events/Event.description: removes a handler function from event object ev previously assigned using EventHandler expression. Native Wolfram Language Delete also works

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Abs.title: AbsoluteThickness
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Abs.description: is used to control the visible thickness of lines used in Graphics. The displayed is not affected by scaling or zooming the plot.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Arr.title: Arrow
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Arr.description: Plots an arrow with a fixed head-size from point 1 to point 2

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Dir.title: Directive
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Dir.description: Used for styling plots or 2D graphics

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Gra.title: Graphics
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Gra.description: represents a two-dimensional graphical image. This is a fundamental expression, which is produced by all 2D plotting functions

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Ima.title: Image
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Ima.description: Represents a raster image and plots the list of pixel's colors to a canvas used in notebooks

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Ins.title: Inset
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Ins.description: a graphics object, that allows to put another Graphics into the canvas. pos has to be a 2D vector, that specifies the position of the inset.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Lin.title: Line
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Lin.description: the representation of a line going though the points {x1,y1}, {x2,y2}

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Sho.title: Show
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Sho.description: Is not supported in wljs-graphics-d3 for now

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Sty.title: Style
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Sty.description: A wrapper that can be used for Text . The following options can be provided

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/SVG.title: SVGAttribute
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/SVG.description: Allows to directly set SVG attribute to a 2D graphics object

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Tex.title: Text
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics/Tex.description: Represents an arbitrary text label placed as a Graphics object

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics3D/S.title: SpotLight
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Graphics3D/S.description: places a fake source of light in a 3D scene (see Graphics3D)

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/Button.title: ButtonView
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/Button.description: This is an internal part of InputButton

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/Editor.title: EditorView
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/Editor.description: A view component to spawn an code-editor (fully functional)

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/FileUp.title: FileUploadView
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/FileUp.description: This is an internal part of InputFile

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputB.title: InputButton
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputB.description: creates a button component and returns EventObject.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputF.title: InputFile
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputF.description: outputs as a drag & drop file-form used to handle file input

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputG.title: InputGroup
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputG.description: groups different event-generators such as InputRange, InputButton or in general EventObject into a new EventObject

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputR.title: InputRange
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputR.description: creates a basic combo of a slider and numerical input field and returns EventObject.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputS.title: InputSpoiler
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputS.description: hides an input element to a spoiler. It does not affect an event object, but changes view of EventObject

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputT.title: InputTable
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputT.description: it places a sort of small Excel-like table editor for list provided. This is a great solution for a large tables, since it does support lazy loading from a server

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputT.title: InputText
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputT.description: creates an event-generator for an input-text field and returns EventObject

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputT.title: InputToggle
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/InputT.description: creates a toggle (checkbox) component and returns EventObject.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/RangeV.title: RangeView
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/RangeV.description: This is an internal (low-level) part of InputRange

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/Slider.title: Slider
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/Slider.description: This is not supported. Please, use alternative way InputRange

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/TextVi.title: TextView
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/TextVi.description: This is an internal part of InputText

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/Toggle.title: ToggleView
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Input/Toggle.description: This is an internal part of InputToggle

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.title: CellHashStorage
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.description: A global Javascript object that stores all cells of the notebook

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.title: core
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.description: Global context in Javascript engine, where all functions of WLJS Interpreter are stored.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.title: downloadByURL
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.description: forces page to download a file given by url

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.title: InstancesHashMap
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.description: A global Javascript object that stores all containers including virtual containers used on a page

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.title: interpretate
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.description: An access to WLJS Interpreter, that can evaluate arbitrary Wolfram Expressions expr in a form of ExpressionJSON  and providing env object to all nested expressions

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.title: ObjectHashMap
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.description: A global Javascript object that stores all data for normal containers including references to InstancesHashMap entities

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.title: openawindow
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.description: opens a window given by url

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.title: server
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.description: A global object, that gives an access to sever's API (if server is available). Usually server is Wolfram Kernel connected via WebSockets protocol or HTTP/POST

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.title: setInnerHTML
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.description: sets the HTML content of the element and evaluating the included `` tags as well

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.title: uuidv4
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Javascript A.description: generates a unique identifier as a string

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Arr.title: ArrayPlot
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Arr.description: Generates a plot, where values are shown in a discrete array of blocks

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Bar.title: BarChart
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Bar.description: generates a bar chart for a list of heights

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Bub.title: BubbleChart
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Bub.description: creates a bubble chart for a list of triples

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Con.title: ContourPlot
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Con.description: Generates a contour plot of $f$ as a function of $x$ and $y$

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Den.title: DensityPlot
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Den.description: makes a density plot of f as a function of x and y

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Lis.title: ListCurvePathPlot
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Lis.description: Plots a curve that corresponds to a smooth path through the specified points

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Lis.title: ListLinePlot
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Lis.description: Plots a line like Plot through the list of points provided

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Lis.title: ListLinePlotly
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Lis.description: An alternative plotting function to ListLinePlot, that supports dynamic updates, panning, zoom out of the box

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Lis.title: ListVectorPlot
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Lis.description: Plot the vector field interpolated from a specified set of vectors

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Mat.title: MatrixPlot
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Mat.description: Plots a 2D array with an arbitrary data inside with axes

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Plo.title: Plot
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Plo.description: A Swiss knife for displaying 2D data

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Plo.title: Plotly
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Plo.description: An alternative plotting function to Plot that uses Plotly.js

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Ran.title: RandomImage
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Ran.description: Generates a raster Image with a given size and distribution. Only RGB space is supported. The maximum value is limited to 255 for each channel

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Sta.title: StackedListPlot
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Sta.description: plots lines for each of the $datai$, with the $i^$ curve being the accumulation of values in $data1$ through $data_i$

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Str.title: StreamPlot
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Str.description: Generates a stream plot of the vector field ${vx,vy}$ as a function of $x$ and $y$

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Vec.title: VectorPlot
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Vec.description: Generates a vector plot of the vector field ${vx,vy}$ as a function of $x$ and $y$

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Vec.title: VectorPlot3D
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Plotting/Vec.description: Generates a 3D vector plot of the vector field {vx,vy,vz} as a function of $x$, $y$, and $z$

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.title: Alert
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.description: creates a pop-up message (dialog) in a user's opened window. Acts like alert in Javascript language.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.title: AttachDOM
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.description: attached a DOM element from the page found by id to the container, where this expression is evaluated

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.title: FlipSymbols
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.description: swaps the content (down values) of the given symbols and fires update on dependent containers

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.title: FrontEditorSelected
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.description: returns the selected line from the input/output cell's of the last focused editor as a string.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.title: ReadClipboard
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.description: Returns a clipboard data of a user as a string

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.title: TalkKernel
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.description: exports an arbitrary object from the frontend to Wolfram Kernel as JSON string and applies handler function to it.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.title: TalkMaster
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.description: the same as TalkKernel, but send the result to a master Wolfram kernel instead.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.title: WindowScope
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Fronte.description: returns Javascript object name defined in the global context.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/LeakyM.title: LeakyModule
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/LeakyM.description: Module that always leaks memory on-purpose

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Notebo.title: CellPrint
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Notebo.description: prints an output cell after the evaluated input cell with a content str provided. Can be used for creating progress bars or other dynamics elements that can help to monitor the state.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Notebo.title: EvaluationCell
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Notebo.description: takes an identifier of an output cell generated after the evaluation. Can be used as EventObject for EventHandler to attach handlers to an output cell or to print another cell after.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Notebo.title: GlobalThrottle
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Notebo.description: sets a throttling value for event generators such as InputText, InputRange and etc, so that they will not fire too often overloading the Wolfram Kernel.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Notebo.title: NotebookStore
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Notebo.description: Sometimes it is easier to ship notebook together with the data it depends on. However, not as a text encoded using BASE64 pasted into a notebook cell - it would just kill the performance, but as a dedicated inner structure, that can be exposed using NotebookStore

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Notebo.title: ParentCell
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Notebo.description: asks master kernel to find an identifier of the parent cell (usually an input cell) of the given output cell.

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Slides.title: SlideEvent
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Slides.description: An event-marker for the given slide of the presentation used in RevealJS plugin

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Timers.title: SetInterval
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Timers.description: Creates an asynchronous task, which is repeated with a period (milliseconds)

frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Timers.title: SetTimeout
frontend/Outdated/Reference/Tools/Timers.description: Creates an asynchronous task, which will be executed once after period (milliseconds)

frontend/Outdated/Troubleshooting.title: Troubleshooting
frontend/Outdated/Troubleshooting.description: If something is not working as intended, please, post an issue on a Github with the data evaluated on your Wolfram Kernel, such as

frontend/Outdated/Tutorial/Dynamics.title: Dynamics
frontend/Outdated/Tutorial/Dynamics.description: The way how dynamics work is quite different compared to Wolfram Mathematica. The key changes were made for the sake of performance and control (or imagination of  @JerryI - maintainer)

frontend/Outdated/Tutorial/Export notebo.title: Export notebook
frontend/Outdated/Tutorial/Export notebo.description: Since all magic happens inside the browser using plain Javascript, it is extremely easy to export notebook to a standalone HTML file or even React component to embed it on website (blog).

frontend/Outdated/Tutorial/GUI Overview.title: GUI Overview

frontend/Outdated/Tutorial/Input element.title: Input elements
frontend/Outdated/Tutorial/Input element.description: Usually, every UI element in a cell is Event generator, i.e. EventObject[] with a field view, which is shown on output. Unlike Mathematica, WLJS Frontend uses event-based approach, so you have to bind a handler function to each interactive element you used

frontend/Outdated/Tutorial/Overview.title: Overview
frontend/Outdated/Tutorial/Overview.description: The whole notebook interface is made using plain Javascript, HTML powered by a Wolfram WebServer  and template engine running locally on a Wolfram Kernel. It means you can work remotely by running a server anywhere you want.

frontend/Outdated/Tutorial/Plugins.title: Plugins
frontend/Outdated/Tutorial/Plugins.description: WLJS Frontend uses a custom package manager to download, update and store extensions from any suitable Github repo. At the first startup it extracts them to a local Packages folder, where one can freely edit and explore them.
